No source-material download link is published (see ../../docs/LICENSING.md).

This source is a work of the United States Government, prepared by the GAO, and is
therefore NOT subject to copyright protection in the United States (17 U.S.C. 105).
GAO's own notice on the product states:

    "This is a work of the U.S. government and is not subject to copyright protection
     in the United States. The published product may be reproduced and distributed in
     its entirety without further permission from GAO."

Caveat (stated by GAO): the published product may contain copyrighted images or other
material whose separate reproduction could require permission from the copyright holder.
This pack reproduces no such third-party material — it contains only synthesized,
transformed reference notes — so the caveat does not apply to this pack's content.
In particular, two embedded items the source attributes to third parties are paraphrased
as text rather than reproduced: the cyclic "process for creating and maintaining reliable
schedules" (Figure 1 / Table 1, adapted from Keith D. Hornbacher) and the strategies-for-
recovery-and-acceleration table (attributed to GAO and NDIA).

